author: @YU_meineLiebe
text: In the end, these two episodes left me full of tears. Especially when Doyoung said that he doesn't want them to experience the hardship they (the hyungs-NCT127) had experienced for paving the way for Dream and WayV. It hurt so much to remember how much hard work NCT 127 has done, how many hummiliation they have suffered along the way, even until today. TBH, Dream and WayV are great, but remember how NCT 127 has always been there for them. As Doyoung said, being a new member of an existing group is somehow easier rather than being the new group on its own. And NCT 127 has always been supporting them right and left, being good hyungs, introducing them to the society, etc. Of course we all know that the maknaes groups are so talented, but does the fans know how much sacrifice the hyungs have made in order to make the maknaes shines? SM is famous to pairing the senior group with the younger, and later to stop promoting the senior group in order to highlighy the junior more (eg. look at example of how they have halted EXO's promotions nowadays). While in NCT 127 itself there are still members that are underused and mistreated, the NCT 127 are still very supportive to every new members, and for me it needs great appreciation.

author: @YU_meineLiebe
text: NCT 127 line up needs to be here as well. but probably has to be on different segment than Dream and WayV, just to be safe (no one wants the maknaes got hurt from their superstrong hyungs). Yuta will punch everyone including the managers, Haechan and Doyoung/Doyoung and Taeyong will spill a lot of blood, Jungwoo and Doyoung will flame every fire, Mark and Taeil will be confused, Jaehyun will be mostly laughing. But in every fight Johny will be there as the peacemaker.

author: @bilou7860
text:
Doyoung is really funny, he is the real mom of NCT, he plays with the kids and makes sure they're comfortable when playing with him. He brings so much joy then he will taking care of them. He takes on every role they want to play, he supports them, sometimes get on their side against him, he plays so much fun that the kids are happy too. These are people who are compatible with Doyoung, i feel grateful that the staff chose these people, they are innocent and cute kids. The members are always very grateful to Doyoung and i like to see if he feel the same for the others cause they play and taking care of him like he takes care of everyone.

And not only that I hope nctzens or others can see this side of him too, I don want again people say Doyoung is an easy target, he does that because he just wants to play games whereas the members like to see him angry. I understand that but not for the fans, I hope nctzen can stop saying 'he is cynical, he likes to mock' he is not! He is an expressive and funny person but sad to know people only see him like that, no one tries to guard his heart, people love to see him being attacked . Doyoung is a very kind person. He always wants people to feel comfortable around him. Fans always thank Doyoung for taking good care of their idol, but it's rare to see them doing that for him, usually some will burst out laughing when the members annoy Doyoung, but when Doyoung try to do it the same some will get angry. I really don't understand how their minds work, so I really hope others will take care of him too and have the same justice for him.

I'm sorry but because of this content as a fan I also want to say this as a matter that we always think about. I am very happy to see him being cheerful and having fun here. i like to see him having fun with the members but afterwards i always worry about the fans reaction, i just want him to hear and see the good things, i just want him to get the same justice as the others. I never want him to stay away from his brothers, he is the best when he is with them he is always happy and comfortable with them. I just want us as a part of this family can start to respect him and pay attention to him you can also try to love him too ğŸ’™

if you read this comment I want to say thank you and i apologize cause I use unpleasant words and target other people here, but I take as a real example that I often see on social media. Sorry because this is too long, but I hope someone reads it, hopefully we can understand each other. 
Once again, thank you ğŸ’šğŸ’š

author: @talialeon9
text: I feel for Sungchan and Shotaro, but we all are forgetting that Xiaojun, Hendery, and Yangyang also were very new to being part of NCT as a whole. They had no previous activities with the rest the members or participation in songs. They all trained together that's for sure, but WayV was seen as if it was another group and not a subunit of NCT(for a lot of people). It was until NCT 2020 that we got to see Xiaojun, Hendery, and Yangyang participating for the first time in NCT as a whole group. We also got the official debut for Shotaro and Sungchan, but it was also the debut for Xiaojun, Hendery, and Yangyang. For me, it was a validation and recognition that WayV members were part of NCT idk if I'm making any sense. At the end of the day, I'm so happy and glad that we get all these activities and content of them together because all of them are NCT, regardless!

author: @goldenesorro6925
text:
Idols are supposed to show their affectionate interaction to prove how close they are, and NCT is not an exception. 
Believe me, NCT is absolutely a real family with many different ways of how they treat each other, but due to the operating system (unlimited members), there will be always some doubts that they may not that close. What I love here is NCT (and SM) are not trying to hide the side we don't normally see in idol members' interaction. They can show their love, as well as their awkwardness (series content AWSAZ (It's Awkward But It's Okay)), their conflicts in reality where there is no camera surrounding them (this content tells those things), about how they actually live under the same roof, and how they deal with their arguments.
This content is made somehow in a funny way, but is enough to show their closeness. Because a true relationship is always 2-sided, which undeniably we can love but we can also fight. And this thing makes NCT relationship look more real to me.
And now I truly understand boys got problems between them, as the same as the girl's lol

author: @moontaeren4902
text:
doyoung: i debuted in 2016 right? do you know how much we suffered? 
ohhooo but tbh i actually had this thought ever since nct 2020 happened though and especially since there will be a new nct unit (nct japan and nct hollywood) coming soon makes me keep thinking about this a lot. the members that had debuted earlier had suffered a lot to make their brand name become who they are right now meanwhile the new members came in after their brand name became widely known. I'm so proud of how far the members that debuted in 2016 made it for the team to become who they are right now. but this doesn't mean i dislike any of the new members at all in fact i support and adore them just the same as the members who debuted first. they worked so hard back then till they were able to make their new unit or new members didn't receive the same treatment as them. because to make someone become their fans back then were soo hard due to their confusing concept and there were many people that gave up understanding the concept plus articles always said they were a fail group from sm but look how big they've become now. each unit plus sungtaro contributes a lot to their brand together. doyoung is literally like the representative of the 2016 members though like im pretty sure all of their thoughts are the same as doyoung. it's bittersweet to reminisce the old days but they're glad they could make the new members comfortable and proud with their team now. so as fans, all we need to do is just give our full support and love to them <3 regardless if the company mistreated them etc. please remember to support them cause we are the only one they have. we are the reason they are still here. i don't care if you are a unit stans or solo stans just learn to respect each other and focus on supporting and loving these boys a lot <3 we don't know what the future holds so please stop making useless fan wars just focus on the boys. <3
